from us to make this go away?

16:17.770 --> 16:21.001
Well, that is one
expensive piece of ass.

16:21.040 --> 16:22.530
( man clears throat)

16:36.290 --> 16:39.657
Violet, this was
an amazing meal.

16:42.060 --> 16:44.699
- I'm glad y'all liked it.
- Yep.

16:44.730 --> 16:47.528
Ever since Claire passed,

16:47.570 --> 16:49.128
I don't get many
home-cooked meals.

16:49.170 --> 16:51.161
You know what
I'm talking about, Remy,

16:51.210 --> 16:53.508
after your Shauna passed?

16:53.540 --> 16:55.576
A lot of takeout
and microwave meals.

16:57.580 --> 17:00.469
Well, not a day goes by
that I don't think about her.

17:01.720 --> 17:04.245
And I lost a...

17:04.290 --> 17:06.645
lot of friends
these last few years.

17:06.690 --> 17:09.716
And losing Brother Ernest
was toughest of all.

17:09.760 --> 17:12.729
I never thought
he'd be called before me.

17:12.760 --> 17:15.558
Which is why I'm here.

17:17.700 --> 17:19.588
Because I don't feel
like your hearts are
really in it.

17:19.630 --> 17:21.530
That ain't true,
Mr. Prosper.

17:21.570 --> 17:23.800
- I don't think
you understand--
- Is it true...

17:23.840 --> 17:28.402
that you're planning
on going one harvest,
and then selling?

17:28.440 --> 17:30.305
Because if that's
your attitude,

17:30.350 --> 17:32.568
then that's gonna
be mine as well.

17:34.250 --> 17:37.139
Now, I'll agree to be
your farm manager,

17:37.190 --> 17:39.545
plus the regular salary,

17:44.190 --> 17:47.751
I promise I won't
steer you wrong.

17:50.330 --> 17:52.696
It's gonna take
a lot of hard work,

17:52.730 --> 17:55.233
and if you work together,

17:55.270 --> 17:58.637
like your father
wanted you to,

17:58.670 --> 18:00.479
it can be done.

18:08.750 --> 18:11.389
All right.
That'll work.

18:17.690 --> 18:19.578
Violet, you got another
piece of that pie?

18:19.630 --> 18:22.599
( all laughing )

18:22.630 --> 18:24.723
Absolutely.

18:24.770 --> 18:28.729
I pulled out my best
recipe for Prosper.

18:28.770 --> 18:31.204
Whoa! You tell
Holleood about that?

18:31.240 --> 18:33.208
( all laughing )

18:33.240 --> 18:37.472
* Together we will stand,
divided we'll fall *

18:37.510 --> 18:41.139
* Come on, now, people,
let's get on the ball... *

18:41.180 --> 18:42.738
All right!

18:42.780 --> 18:45.214
After all these years,

18:45.250 --> 18:48.754
planting cane
is still done by hand.

18:48.790 --> 18:51.918
We have 200 acres to cover.

18:51.960 --> 18:54.895
Now, y'all got
your marching orders.

18:54.930 --> 18:57.364
Let's get to work.

18:57.400 --> 18:59.220
Hey, you got any
spare shovels around,
Ralph Angel?

18:59.270 --> 19:01.488
- Yeah, in the shed.
- I'll grab them.

19:01.540 --> 19:04.532
Oh, Remy, no!
Man, it's locked up.

19:04.570 --> 19:05.764
I'ma get it myself.

19:05.810 --> 19:08.233
Don't worry about it.

19:08.280 --> 19:10.373
Go on.

19:10.410 --> 19:14.414
* Come on, come on,
let's work together *

19:14.450 --> 19:16.441
* Now, now, people

19:16.480 --> 19:18.914
* Say now together
we will stand *

19:18.950 --> 19:23.284
* Every boy, girl,
woman and man *

19:23.330 --> 19:25.685
* Oh, yeah

19:29.500 --> 19:31.821
* Oh, look it here,
look it here... *

19:31.870 --> 19:34.839
I don't remember that shed
having a lock on it.

19:37.310 --> 19:39.528
Pa never locked
nothing up.

19:39.570 --> 19:41.800
Now we got all this
new equipment around here,

19:41.840 --> 19:43.341
can't be too careful.

19:46.480 --> 19:49.745
You mind taking Blue
to school for me?

19:49.780 --> 19:51.839
Don't want him
to be late.

19:51.890 --> 19:54.688
- All right.
- * Make someone happy

19:54.720 --> 19:56.813
- * Make someone smile...
- Come on, boy, let's go.

19:56.860 --> 20:00.694
* Let's all work together
and make life worthwhile *

20:00.730 --> 20:03.494
* Let's work together

20:03.530 --> 20:07.466
* Come on, come on,
let's work together *

20:07.500 --> 20:09.297
* Now, now, people

20:09.340 --> 20:11.831
* Say now together
we will stand *

20:11.870 --> 20:16.330
* Every boy, girl,
woman and man *

20:19.010 --> 20:21.342
* Two or three minutes

20:21.380 --> 20:23.587
* Two or three hours

20:23.620 --> 20:25.713
* What do they mean,
now, now *

20:25.750 --> 20:28.583
- * In this life of ours?
- All right!

20:28.620 --> 20:30.429
Take lunch.
One hour.

20:31.660 --> 20:33.855
Bring them in!
Bring them in!

20:33.900 --> 20:35.856
( Ernest whistles,
speaking Spanish )

20:35.900 --> 20:37.595
Prosper:
Come on!

20:37.630 --> 20:39.495
Yeah, come on.

20:41.440 --> 20:42.759
You all right?

20:42.800 --> 20:45.030
Yeah.

20:45.070 --> 20:49.507
Wow. That is literally
backbreaking work.

20:49.540 --> 20:51.679
I feel guilty.

20:51.710 --> 20:53.940
Why?

20:53.980 --> 20:57.586
Well,
I'm leaving after lunch,
but I'll be back tomorrow.

20:59.720 --> 21:03.053
My husband
and son are coming in.

21:03.090 --> 21:04.955
I got to take care
of some personal business.

21:04.990 --> 21:09.927
Oh. Well, we'll have
plenty of work for you
to do when you get back.

21:11.670 --> 21:13.535
Truth be told, I didn't think
you'd be out here

21:13.570 --> 21:14.559
actually doing the work.

21:16.070 --> 21:17.765
Is that right?

21:17.810 --> 21:19.698
I know,
I guess I just assumed

21:19.740 --> 21:20.900
