Man:
St. Josephine's
Loan and Trust Bank.

28:11.820 --> 28:13.310
How may I help you?

28:13.350 --> 28:15.989
Yes, I'd like to wire
some money from my account?

28:16.020 --> 28:18.921
And what's the name
on that account?

28:18.960 --> 28:22.350
Yes, I'm Nova Bordelon
on the Bordelon Farm Account.

28:22.400 --> 28:25.392
All right,
just give me one moment.

28:25.430 --> 28:26.829
And what's the amount?

28:26.870 --> 28:29.737
Yes,
I'd like to wire $10,000

28:29.770 --> 28:31.829
to All Out Bail Bonds.

28:39.880 --> 28:41.745
So, I see you switched up
your shifts, huh?

28:41.780 --> 28:44.487
Working nights now?

28:44.520 --> 28:46.841
All the better for me.

28:49.060 --> 28:52.951
Look, I got something
for you to take with you
when you leave, hear?

28:52.990 --> 28:54.298
Or I could stop by
and see that farm.

28:54.330 --> 28:56.457
Drop off a few boxes.

28:58.530 --> 29:01.829
I said
that's not gonna work.

29:01.870 --> 29:04.100
I said I'm coming by.

29:04.140 --> 29:05.505
What the hell's
wrong with you, young blood?

29:05.540 --> 29:07.838
You better watch yourself
before you hurt yourself.

29:07.880 --> 29:09.939
I ain't doing this
no more.

29:12.310 --> 29:14.312
Come on!

29:14.350 --> 29:15.317
( groans )

29:15.350 --> 29:17.910
Yeah, stand him up!

29:17.950 --> 29:19.941
- Get off me! Get off me!
- Get him up!

29:25.160 --> 29:27.128
( groans )

29:27.160 --> 29:29.299
What the hell
is going on here?

29:31.200 --> 29:33.020
Melvin?

29:35.040 --> 29:38.339
You're lucky those
weren't cell phones.
You'd both be fired.

29:38.370 --> 29:44.149
Now cut the crap
and get back to work.

29:44.180 --> 29:45.545
I can't work
with this dude no more.

29:45.580 --> 29:48.413
I can't.
I ain't doing this no more.

29:48.450 --> 29:51.010
Get back to work,
Ralph Angel,

29:51.050 --> 29:52.312
or you'll be looking
for a new job.

29:52.350 --> 29:55.217
- I'm fine with that.
- What'd you say?

29:55.260 --> 29:57.285
- I'm fine with that.
- You wanna get fired?

29:57.320 --> 29:58.548
No.

29:58.590 --> 30:00.785
I want you to lay me off.

30:02.360 --> 30:05.568
You're fired.

30:05.600 --> 30:09.331
And I'll make sure
your parole officer
is well aware of it.

30:13.610 --> 30:16.431
Yeah, I'll talk to him.

30:16.480 --> 30:20.007
'Cause I think he'd be
interested in seeing how
my check showed every week.

30:22.220 --> 30:26.111
His math might be better
than mine, sir.

30:27.250 --> 30:29.457
Now, lay me off,

30:29.490 --> 30:32.084
and no one got to know.

30:33.390 --> 30:36.097
Get your shit and get out.

30:36.130 --> 30:37.529
* The clay I woke up
was this one *

30:37.560 --> 30:39.323
Will do.

30:39.370 --> 30:41.463
* I can't sit and play
the victim *

30:41.500 --> 30:44.469
* My day's looking better,
my day's looking better...*

30:44.510 --> 30:46.137
You want cucumbers
or carrots?

30:46.170 --> 30:48.434
- Carrots!
- ( knocking at door)

30:55.420 --> 30:59.242
Man:
Are you Ralph Angel Bordelon?

30:59.290 --> 31:01.417
Yes, sir.

31:01.460 --> 31:04.281
